
[1]spiritless

   SPIRITLESS, a.

   1. Destitute of spirits; wanting animation; wanting cheerfulness;
   dejected; depressed.

   2. Destitute of vigor; wanting life, courage or fire; as a spiritless
   slave.

   A man so faint, so spiritless, so dull, so dead in look--

   3. Having no breath; extinct; dead.
